defend against this.

00:16:21.510 --> 00:16:25.860 align:middle line:84%
Lukan's father
understands quickly

00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:31.830 align:middle line:84%
that it's not going to be
possible for the tribes

00:16:31.830 --> 00:16:34.860 align:middle line:84%
to defend themselves
effectively.

00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:39.330 align:middle line:84%
He sees what the
Romans bring with them

00:16:39.330 --> 00:16:43.050 align:middle line:84%
and knows that the
only solution is

00:16:43.050 --> 00:16:45.210 align:middle line:90%
to create a negotiated peace.

00:16:45.210 --> 00:16:48.330 align:middle line:84%
This is after they've gone
on to the battlefield,

00:16:48.330 --> 00:16:49.785 align:middle line:90%
they've tried their best.

00:16:49.785 --> 00:16:52.530 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And Gracila and
Lukan have been separated

00:16:52.530 --> 00:16:55.485 align:middle line:84%
and he's been wounded pretty
severely in battle, actually.

00:16:55.485 --> 00:16:57.322 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: Yes,
Lukan is wounded.

00:16:57.322 --> 00:16:58.530 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: He chose to do it.

00:16:58.530 --> 00:17:00.655 align:middle line:84%
His father tried to get
him out of it, he said, no.

00:17:00.655 --> 00:17:02.875 align:middle line:84%
Again, living to-- if
we're sending the others,

00:17:02.875 --> 00:17:03.675 align:middle line:90%
we're sending me.

00:17:03.675 --> 00:17:04.275 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Exactly.

00:17:04.275 --> 00:17:04.860 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:04.860 --> 00:17:05.829 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Exactly.

00:17:05.829 --> 00:17:12.160 align:middle line:84%
And so when his father
approaches Vespasian and says,

00:17:12.160 --> 00:17:15.329 align:middle line:84%
I want to have a
conversation with you,

00:17:15.329 --> 00:17:19.710 align:middle line:84%
one tribal chieftain to
another commander of legions,

00:17:19.710 --> 00:17:22.109 align:middle line:84%
let's see if we can
find common ground.

00:17:22.109 --> 00:17:25.140 align:middle line:90%
And in fact, they do.

00:17:25.140 --> 00:17:28.140 align:middle line:84%
It is one of my favorite
parts of the story.

00:17:28.140 --> 00:17:30.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's one of my
favorite parts of all four

00:17:30.390 --> 00:17:31.020 align:middle line:90%
books, is that.

00:17:31.020 --> 00:17:31.695 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Is it?

00:17:31.695 --> 00:17:31.920 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:17:31.920 --> 00:17:32.520 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Me too.

00:17:32.520 --> 00:17:33.320 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:33.320 --> 00:17:35.865 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: Because here
are these purported enemies.

00:17:35.865 --> 00:17:40.980 align:middle line:84%
And you know, we have this
stereotype of the good guy,

00:17:40.980 --> 00:17:42.870 align:middle line:90%
the bad guy.

00:17:42.870 --> 00:17:45.560 align:middle line:90%
We've got to come and vanquish.

00:17:45.560 --> 00:17:48.780 align:middle line:84%
We've got to hold our
ground against the evil.

00:17:48.780 --> 00:17:52.350 align:middle line:84%
And rather than falling
into that caricature,

00:17:52.350 --> 00:17:58.080 align:middle line:84%
they come together as two
intelligent, capable leaders

00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:02.700 align:middle line:84%
who communicate authentically
with each other.

00:18:02.700 --> 00:18:05.880 align:middle line:84%
Lukan's father
doesn't say, well,

00:18:05.880 --> 00:18:07.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm here because I know that--

00:18:07.830 --> 00:18:13.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm doing you a favor because
we could overcome your invasion.

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:17.040 align:middle line:84%
He says, I realize
the position we're in.

00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:22.740 align:middle line:84%
Isn't there a way for us to
come to an agreement that

00:18:22.740 --> 00:18:25.350 align:middle line:84%
allows our
communities to remain,

00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:27.523 align:middle line:84%
that gives Rome
some presence here--

00:18:27.523 --> 00:18:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Whatever resources
and whatever they're looking

00:18:29.940 --> 00:18:30.740 align:middle line:90%
for, yeah.

00:18:30.740 --> 00:18:35.740 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: So that we can all
find a way to live together,

00:18:35.740 --> 00:18:37.060 align:middle line:90%
which is--

00:18:37.060 --> 00:18:37.860 align:middle line:90%
it's a totally--

00:18:37.860 --> 00:18:38.490 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It was so beautiful.

00:18:38.490 --> 00:18:40.000 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: --different
paradigm from--

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:40.262 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: The thoughts.

00:18:40.262 --> 00:18:41.062 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Yeah.

00:18:41.062 --> 00:18:43.695 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: The dialogue were
so crystal clear and logical.

00:18:43.695 --> 00:18:44.610 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: I know.

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:47.820 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And honoring of
what is instead of the delusion

00:18:47.820 --> 00:18:50.220 align:middle line:84%
and ego that goes into
what we know as war now.

00:18:50.220 --> 00:18:51.095 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Exactly.

00:18:51.095 --> 00:18:52.178 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It's beautiful.

00:18:52.178 --> 00:18:56.940 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: So then, that
