00:21:07.960 --> 00:21:12.100 align:middle line:84%
to a woman who fell on
misfortune and became a slave.

00:21:12.100 --> 00:21:16.900 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about her and
what Greek and Roman times

00:21:16.900 --> 00:21:19.010 align:middle line:90%
were like in terms of slavery.

00:21:19.010 --> 00:21:20.590 align:middle line:90%
We don't understand.

00:21:20.590 --> 00:21:25.180 align:middle line:84%
Up to half the population
in Rome were slaves.

00:21:25.180 --> 00:21:27.100 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about that
and how one became

00:21:27.100 --> 00:21:29.050 align:middle line:90%
a slave, accidentally even.

00:21:29.050 --> 00:21:33.010 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: Graci's
mother was in a family--

00:21:33.010 --> 00:21:35.710 align:middle line:90%
a moderately wealthy family.

00:21:35.710 --> 00:21:39.820 align:middle line:84%
Her father was a merchant
who got overextended

00:21:39.820 --> 00:21:44.080 align:middle line:84%
and then took out more loans and
became even more overextended.

00:21:44.080 --> 00:21:49.580 align:middle line:84%
And as a result, the entire
family was thrown into slavery.

00:21:49.580 --> 00:21:51.950 align:middle line:84%
Graci's mother,
who thought she was

00:21:51.950 --> 00:21:56.840 align:middle line:84%
going to lead a
relatively good life,

00:21:56.840 --> 00:22:00.950 align:middle line:84%
ended up not only resenting
the slavery but, of course,

00:22:00.950 --> 00:22:03.260 align:middle line:84%
resenting every
aspect of her life

00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:06.320 align:middle line:84%
because it wasn't at all
what she anticipated.

00:22:06.320 --> 00:22:10.620 align:middle line:84%
Gave birth to Graci,
resented the daughter.

00:22:10.620 --> 00:22:21.590 align:middle line:84%
So Graci was born into the most
difficult situation imaginable

00:22:21.590 --> 00:22:26.400 align:middle line:84%
and yet she was given
an opportunity to learn.

00:22:26.400 --> 00:22:28.850 align:middle line:84%
I don't want-- don't have
to go into detail how,

00:22:28.850 --> 00:22:30.560 align:middle line:90%
but she was educated.

00:22:30.560 --> 00:22:33.740 align:middle line:10%
And because of her
ability to work

00:22:33.740 --> 00:22:37.620 align:middle line:10%
with spices which began
in Atlantis and then

00:22:37.620 --> 00:22:42.170 align:middle line:10%
on into Britannia,
and then now she

00:22:42.170 --> 00:22:46.370 align:middle line:10%
becomes a helper, a
slave in the kitchen

00:22:46.370 --> 00:22:53.170 align:middle line:10%
and creates magnificent
sauces out of these spices.

00:22:53.170 --> 00:22:58.450 align:middle line:84%
It ends up just transforming how
this family have their meals.

00:22:58.450 --> 00:23:01.030 align:middle line:90%
How much they enjoy their meals.

00:23:01.030 --> 00:23:08.590 align:middle line:84%
Lucan, on the other hand, is
born into a very powerful,

00:23:08.590 --> 00:23:11.080 align:middle line:90%
highly--

00:23:11.080 --> 00:23:14.230 align:middle line:90%
very wealthy family in Rome.

00:23:14.230 --> 00:23:17.530 align:middle line:84%
It's the sort of epitome
of the patriarch.

00:23:17.530 --> 00:23:21.910 align:middle line:84%
His father expects him to
live out the family legacy,

00:23:21.910 --> 00:23:27.890 align:middle line:84%
be a senator, agree to an
arranged marriage with someone

00:23:27.890 --> 00:23:32.330 align:middle line:84%
else from a wealthy family
so we can combine our wealth

00:23:32.330 --> 00:23:34.430 align:middle line:90%
and expand our power.

00:23:34.430 --> 00:23:37.340 align:middle line:90%
So he is on that trajectory.

00:23:37.340 --> 00:23:42.350 align:middle line:84%
Graci is a slave, she ends
up being taken to Rome.

00:23:42.350 --> 00:23:48.320 align:middle line:84%
She's serving in the kitchen,
creates deliciousness

00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:53.780 align:middle line:84%
for our banquet, and
Lucan tastes her food

00:23:53.780 --> 00:23:55.430 align:middle line:90%
and recognizes it.

00:23:55.430 --> 00:23:59.270 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: He recognizes
the spice combinations.

00:23:59.270 --> 00:24:02.000 align:middle line:84%
>>MCKIBBIN: And she comes
out, because they're so

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:07.870 align:middle line:84%
blown away by the meal
and he recognizes her.

00:24:07.870 --> 00:24:13.720 align:middle line:84%
But they can never come together
because it's a law in Rome

00:24:13.720 --> 00:24:17.140 align:middle line:84%
that senators can
never marry either

00:24:17.140 --> 00:24:20.380 align:middle line:90%
a slave or a freed woman.

00:24:20.380 --> 00:24:24.790 align:middle line:84%
So even if she's freed,
they can never be married.

00:24:24.790 --> 00:24:27.460 align:middle line:84%
They can never be
legally together.

00:24:27.460 --> 00:24:32.185 align:middle line:84%
And that's the situation they're
thrown into when they meet.

00:24:32.185 --> 00:24:34.570 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And she has been
gracious enough in her own

00:24:34.570 --> 00:24:36.280 align:middle line:90%
life, understanding her lot.

00:24:36.280 --> 00:24:38.170 align:middle line:84%
This is what she-- just
what she's born into.

00:24:38.170 --> 00:24:40.630 align:middle line:84%
It's not like you
had a lot of choices.

00:24:40.630 --> 00:24:42.430 align:middle line:84%
To feel grateful for
the fact that she

00:24:42.430 --> 00:24:45.130 align:middle line:84%
was elevated because
of her cooking skills

00:24:45.130 --> 00:24:47.090 align:middle line:90%
and she's accepted this.

00:24:47.090 --> 00:24:50.800 align:middle line:84%
And so when they asked to meet
face to face, he recognizes her

00:24:50.800 --> 00:24:53.980 align:middle line:84%
but she doesn't seem to be
seeing those possibilities

00:24:53.980 --> 00:24:55.135 align:middle line:90%
right away.

00:24:55.135 --> 00:24:57.845 align:middle line:84%
She is a slave
working the kitchen.

00:24:57.845 --> 00:24:58.645 align:middle line:90%
She's a cook.

00:24:58.645 --> 00:24:59.860 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: She is.

00:24:59.860 --> 00:25:02.830 align:middle line:84%
And she says, we
may love each other

00:25:02.830 --> 00:25:04.420 align:middle line:90%
but we can never be together.

00:25:04.420 --> 00:25:05.472 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:25:05.472 --> 00:25:06.805 align:middle line:90%
And she was pretty firm on that.

00:25:06.805 --> 00:25:07.300 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: She was.

00:25:07.300 --> 00:25:09.800 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And he was the one
that, actually, fought for it.

00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:11.420 align:middle line:84%
We'll go into that
in a little bit.

00:25:11.420 --> 00:25:13.600 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things
that was interesting here

00:25:13.600 --> 00:25:16.960 align:middle line:84%
is, during that
lifetime, because she

00:25:16.960 --> 00:25:21.490 align:middle line:84%
was a favored person for
making this delectable cuisine

00:25:21.490 --> 00:25:25.910 align:middle line:84%
for everybody in Rome, she
was granted certain favors.

00:25:25.910 --> 00:25:30.040 align:middle line:84%
Now, remind me of how she
came across these manuscripts

00:25:30.040 --> 00:25:31.600 align:middle line:90%
because she was--

00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:33.070 align:middle line:90%
educated she could read.

00:25:33.070 --> 00:25:37.510 align:middle line:84%
She came across
manuscripts about Yehshua

00:25:37.510 --> 00:25:39.490 align:middle line:90%
from 100 years prior.

00:25:39.490 --> 00:25:40.720 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about that.

00:25:40.720 --> 00:25:46.150 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: So she
discovers that--

00:25:46.150 --> 00:25:47.740 align:middle line:84%
well, of course,
she can read and she

00:25:47.740 --> 00:25:49.600 align:middle line:90%
learned to read in Greek.

00:25:49.600 --> 00:25:55.050 align:middle line:84%
And her owner who
loves her, knows her

00:25:55.050 --> 00:25:57.750 align:middle line:84%
and loves her in his
own way because he's

00:25:57.750 --> 00:26:01.900 align:middle line:90%
from the previous two lifetimes.

00:26:01.900 --> 00:26:05.460 align:middle line:84%
He, in fact, is Lucan's
father in Britannia.

00:26:05.460 --> 00:26:09.640 align:middle line:84%
So he takes her under his
wing and says, here's a book.

00:26:09.640 --> 00:26:11.250 align:middle line:90%
Here's a book you might enjoy.

00:26:11.250 --> 00:26:12.690 align:middle line:90%
A book from my collection.

00:26:12.690 --> 00:26:19.020 align:middle line:84%
And she reads about him and
discovers that, in fact, she

00:26:19.020 --> 00:26:24.510 align:middle line:84%
not only is able to
relate to the story,

00:26:24.510 --> 00:26:30.720 align:middle line:84%
but she's deeply affected by
all of the teachings of Yehshua.

00:26:30.720 --> 00:26:33.580 align:middle line:84%
She knows-- she deeply
believes that he,

00:26:33.580 --> 00:26:35.280 align:middle line:90%
in fact, was a prophet.

00:26:35.280 --> 00:26:40.680 align:middle line:84%
This is before any organized
religion really has come about.

00:26:40.680 --> 00:26:43.165 align:middle line:84%
This is what the pure,
early teachings--

00:26:43.165 --> 00:26:43.965 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:26:43.965 --> 00:26:46.590 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: --of
Yehshua and his followers

00:26:46.590 --> 00:26:48.840 align:middle line:90%
and their experiences with him.

00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:52.500 align:middle line:84%
And so that gives
her an opportunity

00:26:52.500 --> 00:26:56.070 align:middle line:84%
to believe deeply
in something else.

00:26:56.070 --> 00:27:00.150 align:middle line:84%
If she can't exactly
believe in the love

00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:03.990 align:middle line:84%
she shares with Lucan, which
is real, but it's impossible.

00:27:03.990 --> 00:27:06.000 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But
unexpressed, yeah.

00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:11.040 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: She can believe in
the stories of Yehshua as told

00:27:11.040 --> 00:27:12.930 align:middle line:90%
by his followers.

00:27:12.930 --> 00:27:15.840 align:middle line:90%
And so that gives her--

00:27:15.840 --> 00:27:23.070 align:middle line:84%
it really provides a source
of solace for her and peace

00:27:23.070 --> 00:27:26.220 align:middle line:84%
and comfort even as they
undergo the difficulties

00:27:26.220 --> 00:27:28.315 align:middle line:90%
they face in that lifetime.

00:27:28.315 --> 00:27:31.790 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: What also happens
is he does go on with great,

00:27:31.790 --> 00:27:35.040 align:middle line:84%
great resistance because
they love each other.

00:27:35.040 --> 00:27:37.220 align:middle line:84%
It's now-- it's known,
they love each other.

00:27:37.220 --> 00:27:41.810 align:middle line:84%
With great resistance, he does
go into an arranged marriage.

00:27:41.810 --> 00:27:43.710 align:middle line:90%
We won't get into any of that.

00:27:43.710 --> 00:27:46.010 align:middle line:84%
But there is so much
grace in this story

00:27:46.010 --> 00:27:48.830 align:middle line:84%
because in spite of
the circumstance,

00:27:48.830 --> 00:27:52.550 align:middle line:84%
the two are allowed to be
together in a certain way.

00:27:52.550 --> 00:27:57.640 align:middle line:84%
And well, she's allowed to
continue doing what she does

00:27:57.640 --> 00:27:59.350 align:middle line:90%
and he does what he does.

00:27:59.350 --> 00:28:01.310 align:middle line:90%
He has family and so forth.

00:28:01.310 --> 00:28:03.100 align:middle line:84%
But there is a real
grace and beauty

00:28:03.100 --> 00:28:05.200 align:middle line:84%
that comes in later
on in the story

00:28:05.200 --> 00:28:08.020 align:middle line:90%
between his wife and Graci.

00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:15.200 align:middle line:84%
And that's another element
of really not just grace,

00:28:15.200 --> 00:28:19.730 align:middle line:84%
but honoring relationship
in an open way.

00:28:19.730 --> 00:28:24.500 align:middle line:84%
Honoring relationship in a way
of recognition and true honesty

00:28:24.500 --> 00:28:26.240 align:middle line:84%
with self that you,
again, you don't

00:28:26.240 --> 00:28:27.650 align:middle line:90%
see in modern relationships.

00:28:27.650 --> 00:28:30.060 align:middle line:84%
You don't see in relationships
very often at all.

00:28:30.060 --> 00:28:32.030 align:middle line:84%
And that's exemplified
even in this kind

00:28:32.030 --> 00:28:35.105 align:middle line:84%
of complicated triangle that
ends up occurring, right?

00:28:35.105 --> 00:28:38.880 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: Well, his
wife Euphemia says,

00:28:38.880 --> 00:28:41.415 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to be in this
arranged marriage either.

00:28:41.415 --> 00:28:42.215 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:28:42.215 --> 00:28:45.200 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: But out of
respect for each other--

00:28:45.200 --> 00:28:49.130 align:middle line:84%
they did have respect for
each other and to some extent,

00:28:49.130 --> 00:28:52.160 align:middle line:84%
affection, but he told
her at the very beginning

00:28:52.160 --> 00:28:54.195 align:middle line:84%
of their marriage,
I love someone else.

00:28:54.195 --> 00:28:54.995 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:28:54.995 --> 00:28:56.780 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: I
will be respectful,

00:28:56.780 --> 00:28:58.600 align:middle line:84%
we'll have children,
but my heart is--

00:28:58.600 --> 00:29:00.350 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But know
my heart is elsewhere.

00:29:00.350 --> 00:29:00.890 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Yes.

00:29:00.890 --> 00:29:01.340 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:01.340 --> 00:29:02.920 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: And she
understands that.

00:29:02.920 --> 00:29:03.720 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:03.720 --> 00:29:07.010 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: So after they've
had their family and she

00:29:07.010 --> 00:29:13.400 align:middle line:84%
realizes Graci's circumstances,
she decides that she's done

00:29:13.400 --> 00:29:14.550 align:middle line:90%
what she needed to do.

00:29:14.550 --> 00:29:15.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:29:15.350 --> 00:29:17.720 align:middle line:84%
And then wonderful
things happened.

00:29:17.720 --> 00:29:19.587 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: We won't
say what they are.

00:29:19.587 --> 00:29:23.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Then, unwonderful
things happen and, again,

00:29:23.180 --> 00:29:27.080 align:middle line:84%
we have to remember that
at this time period,

00:29:27.080 --> 00:29:30.080 align:middle line:84%
Christians are not
popular in Rome.

00:29:30.080 --> 00:29:33.920 align:middle line:84%
They're entertainment in
a bad way, shall we say?

00:29:33.920 --> 00:29:37.490 align:middle line:84%
And so Graci gets
caught up in all of this

00:29:37.490 --> 00:29:42.290 align:middle line:84%
and refuses to back
down on her affection

00:29:42.290 --> 00:29:45.560 align:middle line:84%
for the teachings of
these followers of Yehshua

00:29:45.560 --> 00:29:46.370 align:middle line:90%
in the day.

00:29:46.370 --> 00:29:50.990 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: Lucan has made an
attempt with Marcus Aurelius

00:29:50.990 --> 00:29:56.960 align:middle line:84%
right before he dies to create
some kind of decree to turn

00:29:56.960 --> 00:29:59.690 align:middle line:84%
Rome back into a Republic
and does something--

00:29:59.690 --> 00:30:01.700 align:middle line:90%
and he's not successful.

00:30:01.700 --> 00:30:03.290 align:middle line:90%
Commodus takes over.

00:30:03.290 --> 00:30:06.680 align:middle line:84%
Commodus knows
Lucan's role in this

00:30:06.680 --> 00:30:11.300 align:middle line:84%
and punishes Graci
for being a Christian.

00:30:11.300 --> 00:30:13.820 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now, you didn't
know about Commodus either.

00:30:13.820 --> 00:30:15.170 align:middle line:90%
You didn't know Roman history.

00:30:15.170 --> 00:30:16.700 align:middle line:84%
You hadn't studied
Roman history.

00:30:16.700 --> 00:30:19.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's what makes all
this so shocking, really.

00:30:19.370 --> 00:30:22.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean-- it shows that
you're a very clear Channel,

00:30:22.250 --> 00:30:23.240 align:middle line:90%
I will say that.

00:30:23.240 --> 00:30:27.013 align:middle line:84%
Because I started looking up
everybody and the character

00:30:27.013 --> 00:30:28.430 align:middle line:84%
traits that were
given in the book

00:30:28.430 --> 00:30:30.560 align:middle line:84%
turned out that is the
character of these people

00:30:30.560 --> 00:30:33.240 align:middle line:84%
and what they were
known as historically.

00:30:33.240 --> 00:30:34.850 align:middle line:90%
So you nailed that character.

00:30:34.850 --> 00:30:36.750 align:middle line:90%
Commodus was not a nice person.

00:30:36.750 --> 00:30:39.964 align:middle line:84%
He did not have a
positive effect on Rome

00:30:39.964 --> 00:30:43.375 align:middle line:84%
and he did not
have a kind reign.

00:30:43.375 --> 00:30:44.400 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: No.

00:30:44.400 --> 00:30:46.590 align:middle line:84%
The Christians were
taken to the Colosseum

00:30:46.590 --> 00:30:49.410 align:middle line:84%
for public entertainment
and killed.

00:30:49.410 --> 00:30:50.970 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:30:50.970 --> 00:30:53.850 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: So that story--

00:30:53.850 --> 00:30:58.400 align:middle line:84%
that was a difficult story
for me to write parts of it

00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:01.170 align:middle line:84%
because we want the lovers
to be able to come together.

00:31:01.170 --> 00:31:02.430 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:31:02.430 --> 00:31:06.653 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: This isn't a
classic historical romance

00:31:06.653 --> 00:31:07.695 align:middle line:90%
the way we think of them.

00:31:07.695 --> 00:31:08.280 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:31:08.280 --> 00:31:09.155 align:middle line:90%
It's not Harlequin.

00:31:09.155 --> 00:31:14.010 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: But it is about
how they come together in love.

00:31:14.010 --> 00:31:16.350 align:middle line:90%
They still love each other.

00:31:16.350 --> 00:31:19.050 align:middle line:84%
How-- and does
that love survive?

00:31:19.050 --> 00:31:20.520 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it does.

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:21.385 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it does.

00:31:21.385 --> 00:31:22.185 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:31:22.185 --> 00:31:22.985 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: But.

00:31:22.985 --> 00:31:26.700 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: --Graci is
very wounded by this whole

00:31:26.700 --> 00:31:27.840 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:33.150 align:middle line:84%
She is imprisoned at
the end and is going

00:31:33.150 --> 00:31:34.740 align:middle line:90%
to be taken to the Colosseum.

00:31:34.740 --> 00:31:39.540 align:middle line:84%
And he says to her, renounce
your belief in Yehshua.

00:31:39.540 --> 00:31:41.670 align:middle line:90%
And she says, I can't.

00:31:41.670 --> 00:31:43.020 align:middle line:90%
I won't.

00:31:43.020 --> 00:31:43.860 align:middle line:90%
I won't.

00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:47.030 align:middle line:90%


00:31:47.030 --> 00:31:51.900 align:middle line:84%
I won't walk away from that
in order to save my life.

00:31:51.900 --> 00:31:54.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, she's very
clear about that.

00:31:54.480 --> 00:31:58.460 align:middle line:84%
It was so wounding for her
that she doesn't come back

00:31:58.460 --> 00:32:01.055 align:middle line:90%
for 1,500 years to be with him.

00:32:01.055 --> 00:32:02.993 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now, let
me ask you a question.

00:32:02.993 --> 00:32:04.910 align:middle line:84%
Did you get anywhere in
there because you only

00:32:04.910 --> 00:32:05.675 align:middle line:90%
get what you get.

00:32:05.675 --> 00:32:06.320 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: I know.

00:32:06.320 --> 00:32:07.490 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So it's not like
they're going to tell you

00:32:07.490 --> 00:32:08.960 align:middle line:90%
everything in between.

00:32:08.960 --> 00:32:14.120 align:middle line:84%
Did you get a sense that she
had incarnated during that 1,500

00:32:14.120 --> 00:32:17.030 align:middle line:84%
years but she had not
incarnated at a time where they

00:32:17.030 --> 00:32:18.410 align:middle line:90%
would hook up together again?

00:32:18.410 --> 00:32:23.420 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: He gave up the
opportunity to be with her

00:32:23.420 --> 00:32:27.770 align:middle line:84%
during that 1,500 years so
she could reincarnate and work

00:32:27.770 --> 00:32:29.360 align:middle line:90%
through the wounding.

00:32:29.360 --> 00:32:34.445 align:middle line:84%
She did that because
of her rootedness

00:32:34.445 --> 00:32:38.600 align:middle line:84%
in Yehshua and then as
it became Christianity.

00:32:38.600 --> 00:32:42.650 align:middle line:84%
And as we've said,
women have not

00:32:42.650 --> 00:32:48.650 align:middle line:84%
had power over their
own lives really ever.

00:32:48.650 --> 00:32:51.170 align:middle line:84%
In the days when she
was reincarnating,

00:32:51.170 --> 00:32:53.240 align:middle line:90%
women had two choices--

00:32:53.240 --> 00:32:58.670 align:middle line:84%
to either-- if they didn't
have money, to be, essentially,

00:32:58.670 --> 00:33:02.780 align:middle line:84%
slaves in a household, if they
did come from a wealthy family,

00:33:02.780 --> 00:33:04.250 align:middle line:90%
to be in an arranged marriage--

00:33:04.250 --> 00:33:05.345 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Or a convent.

00:33:05.345 --> 00:33:08.360 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: --or the
other choice is a convent.

00:33:08.360 --> 00:33:10.850 align:middle line:84%
She chose a convent
because, at least, there

00:33:10.850 --> 00:33:14.360 align:middle line:84%
was a sisterhood there and
they could, to some extent,

00:33:14.360 --> 00:33:16.490 align:middle line:84%
even under the thumb
of the patriarchy,

00:33:16.490 --> 00:33:19.040 align:middle line:90%
they still had some freedoms.

00:33:19.040 --> 00:33:24.290 align:middle line:84%
So she reincarnated as a nun
multiple lifetimes in order

00:33:24.290 --> 00:33:29.600 align:middle line:84%
to heal and take her
power back as a woman

00:33:29.600 --> 00:33:33.517 align:middle line:84%
after that difficult
lifetime of slavery.

00:33:33.517 --> 00:33:34.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Go ahead.

00:33:34.350 --> 00:33:35.580 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: And then--

00:33:35.580 --> 00:33:37.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So then we
come to book number 4.

00:33:37.650 --> 00:33:41.310 align:middle line:10%
So now, it's called
"Give" in 1671.

00:33:41.310 --> 00:33:43.560 align:middle line:10%
So we've let 1,500 years pass.

00:33:43.560 --> 00:33:44.790 align:middle line:10%
Now they're back.

00:33:44.790 --> 00:33:47.790 align:middle line:84%
And in this time, again,
they're worlds apart.

00:33:47.790 --> 00:33:50.700 align:middle line:84%
And Lucan, his
character continues

00:33:50.700 --> 00:33:54.900 align:middle line:84%
to incarnate in positions
that have some kind of stature

00:33:54.900 --> 00:33:57.630 align:middle line:84%
to them throughout
in each of the books.

00:33:57.630 --> 00:34:00.840 align:middle line:84%
And this time, he has stature,
again, but now we go to France,

00:34:00.840 --> 00:34:01.640 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:34:01.640 --> 00:34:03.098 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Provence, France--

00:34:03.098 --> 00:34:04.140 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Love Provence.

00:34:04.140 --> 00:34:05.310 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: I know.

00:34:05.310 --> 00:34:06.452 align:middle line:90%
I wrote this in Provence.

00:34:06.452 --> 00:34:07.410 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, did you?

00:34:07.410 --> 00:34:11.070 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: I was staying with
a friend whose aunt and uncle

00:34:11.070 --> 00:34:14.850 align:middle line:84%
have not one but two
villas in Provence.

00:34:14.850 --> 00:34:18.659 align:middle line:84%
Two weeks-- I wrote this book
in two weeks in Provence.

00:34:18.659 --> 00:34:24.600 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, Luc has inherited
a massive estate

00:34:24.600 --> 00:34:29.270 align:middle line:84%
with a huge chateau and
all kinds of small villages

00:34:29.270 --> 00:34:30.070 align:middle line:90%
around it.

00:34:30.070 --> 00:34:31.830 align:middle line:90%
People working the land.

00:34:31.830 --> 00:34:34.679 align:middle line:84%
He can't stand the
gilt furniture,

00:34:34.679 --> 00:34:39.112 align:middle line:84%
he deplores the decadence
of everyone else

00:34:39.112 --> 00:34:42.614 align:middle line:84%
in his demographic group,
if I can call it that.

00:34:42.614 --> 00:34:44.061 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:34:44.061 --> 00:34:48.840 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: She is born,
actually, in Italy, in Venice.

00:34:48.840 --> 00:34:53.130 align:middle line:84%
She's the daughter of a
senator and his courtesan.

00:34:53.130 --> 00:34:57.030 align:middle line:84%
She's taken, immediately,
to a convent to be raised.

00:34:57.030 --> 00:34:59.040 align:middle line:90%
He dies after six years.

00:34:59.040 --> 00:35:01.860 align:middle line:84%
They can't afford to keep
her, they send her to France

00:35:01.860 --> 00:35:05.980 align:middle line:84%
to another convent
where she is educated.

00:35:05.980 --> 00:35:08.530 align:middle line:84%
Has the opportunity
to take her vows.

00:35:08.530 --> 00:35:10.870 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is what's
interesting because she

00:35:10.870 --> 00:35:14.140 align:middle line:84%
could have taken her
vows one more time as she

00:35:14.140 --> 00:35:16.810 align:middle line:90%
had done in that 1,500 years.

00:35:16.810 --> 00:35:20.770 align:middle line:84%
But she knows, on
some level, that she's

00:35:20.770 --> 00:35:22.520 align:middle line:90%
ready to be out in the world.

00:35:22.520 --> 00:35:25.960 align:middle line:84%
She doesn't know what will
happen, but she's educated,

00:35:25.960 --> 00:35:28.660 align:middle line:84%
she figures she could
earn a living somehow.

00:35:28.660 --> 00:35:32.770 align:middle line:84%
And at that point,
the abyss says, well,

00:35:32.770 --> 00:35:37.360 align:middle line:84%
I happen to know there might
be an opening for a governess.

00:35:37.360 --> 00:35:40.730 align:middle line:90%


00:35:40.730 --> 00:35:44.050 align:middle line:84%
A count has two sons,
his wife has died.

00:35:44.050 --> 00:35:46.150 align:middle line:90%
They need to be educated.

00:35:46.150 --> 00:35:50.260 align:middle line:84%
Maybe, there would be an
opportunity for you there and--

00:35:50.260 --> 00:35:51.620 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:35:51.620 --> 00:35:52.420 align:middle line:90%
There we go.

00:35:52.420 --> 00:35:53.800 align:middle line:90%
They come back together again.

00:35:53.800 --> 00:35:55.910 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:35:55.910 --> 00:35:58.420 align:middle line:84%
And this time in a
different environment

00:35:58.420 --> 00:36:01.000 align:middle line:84%
with less resistance
against them.

00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:03.880 align:middle line:84%
But what was so
beautiful and fascinating

00:36:03.880 --> 00:36:08.030 align:middle line:84%
about that book was, again,
his character and as you say,

00:36:08.030 --> 00:36:08.830 align:middle line:90%
right action.

00:36:08.830 --> 00:36:09.630 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Yes.

00:36:09.630 --> 00:36:11.840 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And being able
to take something that,

00:36:11.840 --> 00:36:14.740 align:middle line:84%
as you say, is just dripping
in decadence and turn it

00:36:14.740 --> 00:36:17.290 align:middle line:84%
into something that's
a benefit for all.

00:36:17.290 --> 00:36:21.340 align:middle line:84%
So they, ultimately, are able
to marry in this book, right?

00:36:21.340 --> 00:36:22.697 align:middle line:90%
So we don't-- that's OK.

00:36:22.697 --> 00:36:23.530 align:middle line:90%
Everyone knows that.

00:36:23.530 --> 00:36:24.940 align:middle line:90%
That's going to happen.

00:36:24.940 --> 00:36:27.563 align:middle line:84%
And she has been wonderful
with his kids, of course,

00:36:27.563 --> 00:36:29.230 align:middle line:84%
they fall in love
with her because she's

00:36:29.230 --> 00:36:32.890 align:middle line:84%
so clever and creative and
makes learning fun for them.

00:36:32.890 --> 00:36:35.740 align:middle line:84%
But it's what happens with
the other people surrounding

00:36:35.740 --> 00:36:38.230 align:middle line:84%
their lives because in
each of these lifetimes

00:36:38.230 --> 00:36:41.260 align:middle line:84%
one thing that happens is,
she does not bear children,

00:36:41.260 --> 00:36:43.060 align:middle line:90%
not in any of these lifetimes.

00:36:43.060 --> 00:36:46.680 align:middle line:84%
So we come back and they're
trying, it's not working.

00:36:46.680 --> 00:36:49.290 align:middle line:84%
But they have this
trip to Paris.

00:36:49.290 --> 00:36:51.720 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
what happens then.

00:36:51.720 --> 00:36:56.110 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: They go to Paris
and he's selling his wine which

00:36:56.110 --> 00:36:56.910 align:middle line:90%
is the--

00:36:56.910 --> 00:36:57.907 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exorbitant prices.

00:36:57.907 --> 00:36:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: And
exorbitant prices.

00:36:59.560 --> 00:37:01.200 align:middle line:84%
It's the best wine
in France and he

00:37:01.200 --> 00:37:04.580 align:middle line:84%
says, if all these wealthy
people are willing to pay--

00:37:04.580 --> 00:37:06.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And I can
fund everything else.

00:37:06.330 --> 00:37:09.420 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: For my wine and I
can fund what I want to do with

00:37:09.420 --> 00:37:11.940 align:middle line:84%
my money, which is
help others, great,

00:37:11.940 --> 00:37:13.740 align:middle line:84%
I'll make the wine
and sell it to them.

00:37:13.740 --> 00:37:20.370 align:middle line:84%
He's doing that and she goes to
the Ile Saint Louis for lunch.

00:37:20.370 --> 00:37:24.060 align:middle line:84%
She's having her-- having
some soup and a little girl

00:37:24.060 --> 00:37:27.420 align:middle line:84%
walks up with a scraggly
stalk of lavender and asks

00:37:27.420 --> 00:37:29.400 align:middle line:90%
if she wants to buy it.

00:37:29.400 --> 00:37:32.940 align:middle line:84%
And she looks at her
and asks if she'd

00:37:32.940 --> 00:37:36.720 align:middle line:84%
like to have some soup and,
maybe, some hot chocolate.

00:37:36.720 --> 00:37:40.980 align:middle line:84%
And she learns that this
girl is living on the street.

00:37:40.980 --> 00:37:42.700 align:middle line:90%
That her mother has died.

00:37:42.700 --> 00:37:44.400 align:middle line:84%
The girl doesn't
know it, but she's

00:37:44.400 --> 00:37:47.670 align:middle line:84%
died because she had to
resort to prostitution

00:37:47.670 --> 00:37:51.175 align:middle line:84%
just to feed them and
even that wasn't enough.

00:37:51.175 --> 00:37:51.975 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:37:51.975 --> 00:37:56.190 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: And the girl has
a best friend whose mother is

00:37:56.190 --> 00:37:58.920 align:middle line:84%
really taking care of them
both, but she's also living

00:37:58.920 --> 00:38:00.300 align:middle line:90%
on the street.

00:38:00.300 --> 00:38:04.308 align:middle line:90%
Very horrible circumstances.

00:38:04.308 --> 00:38:05.725 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But
common for the day.

00:38:05.725 --> 00:38:06.725 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: But common.

00:38:06.725 --> 00:38:10.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is
what Luc abhorred

00:38:10.300 --> 00:38:16.510 align:middle line:84%
about the times with the hideous
decadence and the hideous

00:38:16.510 --> 00:38:21.240 align:middle line:90%
poverty existing side by side.

00:38:21.240 --> 00:38:27.510 align:middle line:84%
So she takes the girl back to
the place where they're staying

00:38:27.510 --> 00:38:34.320 align:middle line:84%
and lets her have a bath and
a nap and Luc arrives home

00:38:34.320 --> 00:38:38.400 align:middle line:90%
and there she is.

00:38:38.400 --> 00:38:41.920 align:middle line:84%
Of course, he loves her
immediately and thinks,

00:38:41.920 --> 00:38:45.000 align:middle line:84%
well, we can't send her
back to the streets.

00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:49.080 align:middle line:84%
So let's, at least, tomorrow
morning, go back with her

00:38:49.080 --> 00:38:51.630 align:middle line:84%
so that the woman
who's been taking care

00:38:51.630 --> 00:38:55.060 align:middle line:84%
of her and the daughter will
know that she's going with us

00:38:55.060 --> 00:38:58.650 align:middle line:84%
and she's going to be OK because
we don't want them to worry.

00:38:58.650 --> 00:39:01.110 align:middle line:90%
And she agrees to go with them.

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:04.680 align:middle line:84%
Of course, what happens is,
all of them go together.

00:39:04.680 --> 00:39:09.900 align:middle line:84%
And they go back and it's the
beginning of just a marvelous

00:39:09.900 --> 00:39:15.390 align:middle line:84%
part of the story because
they are living out

00:39:15.390 --> 00:39:21.390 align:middle line:84%
what Luc and Graciella
want, which is to create--

00:39:21.390 --> 00:39:24.570 align:middle line:84%
if I can call it
this, a democracy

00:39:24.570 --> 00:39:29.080 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of
the France which

00:39:29.080 --> 00:39:31.810 align:middle line:90%
is anything but a democracy.

00:39:31.810 --> 00:39:35.740 align:middle line:84%
Luc shares his profits
with all the people

00:39:35.740 --> 00:39:38.170 align:middle line:84%
who are working the
land, he provides

00:39:38.170 --> 00:39:42.550 align:middle line:84%
opportunities for the children
to get educated and learn

00:39:42.550 --> 00:39:47.540 align:middle line:84%
a trade so that they can, maybe,
rise above where they've been.

00:39:47.540 --> 00:39:48.790 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: He funds a school.

00:39:48.790 --> 00:39:52.060 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: He funds a school.

00:39:52.060 --> 00:39:55.750 align:middle line:84%
He's got a-- and because
he has so much land

00:39:55.750 --> 00:39:59.020 align:middle line:84%
and he has considerable
wealth, he's

00:39:59.020 --> 00:40:03.020 align:middle line:84%
able to do, basically,
whatever he chooses.

00:40:03.020 --> 00:40:07.300 align:middle line:84%
And he chooses something very
different from court life

00:40:07.300 --> 00:40:10.270 align:middle line:84%
and from the aristocracy
living in France.

00:40:10.270 --> 00:40:15.460 align:middle line:84%
It's so fulfilling to see
how they come together

00:40:15.460 --> 00:40:18.835 align:middle line:84%
with the exuberance and the
abundance of their love.

00:40:18.835 --> 00:40:22.150 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, absolutely.

00:40:22.150 --> 00:40:24.070 align:middle line:90%
I have to say, and it is.

00:40:24.070 --> 00:40:26.890 align:middle line:84%
And how everyone that comes in
contact with the two of them

00:40:26.890 --> 00:40:30.400 align:middle line:84%
always benefits from their
relationship with them

00:40:30.400 --> 00:40:34.120 align:middle line:90%
on multitude of levels.

00:40:34.120 --> 00:40:39.670 align:middle line:84%
And I have to say, I
have a friend who is just

00:40:39.670 --> 00:40:41.755 align:middle line:84%
kind of a-- she's
been through life

00:40:41.755 --> 00:40:43.630 align:middle line:84%
and she's kind of seen
it all and done it all

00:40:43.630 --> 00:40:46.000 align:middle line:84%
and she always says,
yeah, I wish I could cry.

00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:48.280 align:middle line:84%
I just can't even
cry about anything.

00:40:48.280 --> 00:40:51.160 align:middle line:90%
And beautiful, beautiful heart.

00:40:51.160 --> 00:40:53.470 align:middle line:90%
But just not a romantic.

00:40:53.470 --> 00:40:55.700 align:middle line:90%
Let's just say that.

00:40:55.700 --> 00:40:59.200 align:middle line:84%
So as I got each of your books
at the very beginning when

00:40:59.200 --> 00:41:01.660 align:middle line:84%
you were first, first
putting them out about one

00:41:01.660 --> 00:41:04.710 align:middle line:84%
at a time initially and then
I'd pass them to her to read.

00:41:04.710 --> 00:41:06.400 align:middle line:90%
She was, oh my god.

00:41:06.400 --> 00:41:08.530 align:middle line:84%
And it turned out
she read the series,

00:41:08.530 --> 00:41:10.120 align:middle line:84%
she went and read
the series again.

00:41:10.120 --> 00:41:13.180 align:middle line:84%
She started sending the series
to everyone and she said,

00:41:13.180 --> 00:41:14.470 align:middle line:90%
I can't stop reading them.

00:41:14.470 --> 00:41:19.990 align:middle line:84%
And I realized I am not going
to settle for a relationship

00:41:19.990 --> 00:41:21.640 align:middle line:90%
unless it feels like that.

00:41:21.640 --> 00:41:26.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to wait no matter how
many incarnations until I find

00:41:26.620 --> 00:41:29.410 align:middle line:84%
that kind of divine
compliment where we can live

00:41:29.410 --> 00:41:31.600 align:middle line:84%
these kinds of
lives of integrity

00:41:31.600 --> 00:41:33.460 align:middle line:84%
because she's a
woman of integrity.

00:41:33.460 --> 00:41:36.070 align:middle line:84%
And so I was just
blown away to watch

00:41:36.070 --> 00:41:39.310 align:middle line:84%
how she was transformed
on some level

00:41:39.310 --> 00:41:43.480 align:middle line:84%
and restored in terms
of her faith in love

00:41:43.480 --> 00:41:45.070 align:middle line:84%
by reading these
books, of course,

00:41:45.070 --> 00:41:46.300 align:middle line:90%
like a lot of other people.

00:41:46.300 --> 00:41:49.180 align:middle line:84%
>> MCKIBBIN: I've heard
something similar from a lot

00:41:49.180 --> 00:41:50.230 align:middle line:90%
of readers.

00:41:50.230 --> 00:41:54.880 align:middle line:84%
And they talk about how I'm
no longer willing to settle,

00:41:54.880 --> 00:41:57.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm no longer
going to compromise

00:41:57.040 --> 00:42:00.130 align:middle line:84%
to make a relationship
work, I'm no longer going

00:42:00.130 --> 00:42:02.560 align:middle line:90%
to turn my back on who I am.

00:42:02.560 --> 00:42:03.860 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:42:03.860 --> 00:42:04.660 align:middle line:90%
All of this.

00:42:04.660 --> 00:42:05.840 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: All of this.

00:42:05.840 --> 00:42:12.070 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, the story isn't
about finding your twin flame,

00:42:12.070 --> 00:42:18.580 align:middle line:84%
it's really about being clear
enough and empowered enough

00:42:18.580 --> 00:42:21.700 align:middle line:84%
in oneself to say,
this is who I am,

00:42:21.700 --> 00:42:24.520 align:middle line:84%
this is who I want to
be in relationship.

00:42:24.520 --> 00:42:28.780 align:middle line:84%
I want to show up in
relationship in these ways.

00:42:28.780 --> 00:42:32.950 align:middle line:84%
If someone can be in
relationship with me

00:42:32.950 --> 00:42:35.840 align:middle line:90%
bringing his best, wonderful.

00:42:35.840 --> 00:42:39.185 align:middle line:84%
If not, I can still
be fully who I am.

00:42:39.185 --> 00:42:39.985 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:42:39.985 --> 00:42:40.785 align:middle line:90%
>> MCKIBBIN: Yeah.

00:42:40.785 --> 00:42:44.240 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And that is the
feeling that's coming up.

00:42:44.240 --> 00:42:46.400 align:middle line:84%
And I think what you just
said is very important.

00:42:46.400 --> 00:42:49.270 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean you have to wait
for your twin flame or divine

00:42:49.270 --> 00:42:51.010 align:middle line:84%
compliment, that
could be a while.

00:42:51.010 --> 00:42:55.840 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't-- it also does
mean there are many people

00:42:55.840 --> 00:42:59.350 align:middle line:84%
on a frequency range level
where their frequency matches

